                            <comment id="17868415" author="gharris1727" created="Wed, 24 Jul 2024 16:02:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=k0b3rit&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;k0b3rit&quot;&gt;k0b3rit&lt;/a&gt; thanks for the bug report!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;config.providers&quot; not being propagated to the connector config is actually a desirable property, as config providers are typically defined in the worker and evaluated on behalf of connectors. However, it appears the same prefix-bug is preventing the MirrorMakerConfig#workerConfig from propagating the config.providers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think you can work around this by specifying &quot;&amp;lt;cluster&amp;gt;.config.providers=env&quot; for each &quot;&amp;lt;cluster&amp;gt;&quot; in the &quot;clusters&quot; config. We can also change this so that workerConfig includes &quot;config.providers&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17868496" author="k0b3rit" created="Wed, 24 Jul 2024 22:05:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gharris1727&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gharris1727&quot;&gt;gharris1727&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yeah, the workaround probably works, but this change could cause headache to other users as well, when they upgrade to 3.7 from an earlier version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
